  "body": "A config file, may be named as `remix-config.js` can be used for all type of configurations we required from user on Remix IDE platform. It will be dedicated to a certain [remix workspace](https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/issues/406) only. \r\n\r\nIt can have plugin based configuration like `version`, `evmVersion`, `optimization` and `auto compile` for `Solidity Compiler` plugin. It also can have settings to enable/disable metadata generation for compiled contracts. Each time a workspace will be loaded, configuration from this config file will be updated for plugins and other places.\r\n\r\nWe need to figure out:\r\n\r\n- [ ] Its Specification\r\n- [ ] How not to make it complicated for beginners\r\n- [ ] Will it be 2-way syncing (If config in compiler plugin is updated, should we update the config file too) (May be this too can be configured through this config file itself)\r\n- [ ] Limitations (Will it be limited to certain/native plugins)\r\n- [ ] Config file can be deleted and users can use of remix default behaviour.",
